  "conclusion": "With rowchunk force-flag forwarding fixed, forcing the full-attention context+gate branch and O projection together to per-row diagnostics is not a repair and no longer reproduces the pre-forwarding rowchunk3 token movement. Rowchunk2 is poisoned (token-red at L6 with L5 layer4 QKV/Z drift), rowchunk3 remains token-red at L6 with L5 layer4 QKV/Z drift, and both rowchunk paths have L8 layer7 attn_input_pre_qkv/query/attn_context/mlp_input failures. The O-bearing context/gate+O suffix is therefore eliminated as a retained-compatible fix under trustworthy forwarded execution, and the earlier pre-forwarding token movement is superseded.",
